  "instruction": "Your generated names are made of few prefixes and suffixes.",
  "y_star": "Certainly! Here's a complete improved response addressing the user's request and feedback:\n\nApologies for any confusion earlier. To create non-generated fantasy planet names, you can combine a variety of prefixes and suffixes to build unique and imaginative names. Based on the prefixes you mentioned\u2014**Astra**, **Celestia**, and **Verdant**\u2014and the suffixes\u2014**dor**, **sia**, and **anth**\u2014here are some fantasy planet names crafted with a mix of these elements:\n\n1. **Celestianth**  \n2. **Verdantia**  \n3. **Astrasor**  \n4. **Celestior**  \n5. **Verdansia**  \n\nBy using multiple prefixes and suffixes, you can create names that feel rich, layered, and deeply rooted in fantasy lore. Feel free to experiment with combinations or add additional elements to suit your worldbuilding needs! Let me know if you'd like more suggestions.",
